Difference between JPA, Hibernate and Spring Data JPA
========================================================

JPA (Java Persistence API):
- JPA is a specification (JSR 338)
- JPA does not have its own implementation
- It only defines rules/interfaces for how ORM should work

Hibernate:
- Hibernate is one of the implementations of JPA
- It is an actual ORM tool that maps Java objects to database tables

Spring Data JPA:
- Spring Data JPA is an abstraction built on top of Hibernate
- It removes boilerplate code needed for persisting data using Hibernate
- Provides ready-made repository interfaces (like JpaRepository) for CRUD operations

Summary:
JPA = specification
Hibernate = implementation of JPA
Spring Data JPA = wrapper/abstraction over Hibernate to reduce boilerplate code